The Alex Jones Show
Sunday, 24 July 2011


[sebaygo1]


The 2 hour Sunday show is typically a review of the past week's news and a look forward to the coming week's events.

The Infowars web site describes today's broadcast as follows.

On this, the Sunday Edition of the Alex Jones Show, Alex talks about the bombing and shootings in Norway and the move by governments to demonize "right-wing extremists" in Europe and the United States as violent terrorists. Alex also talks with an eye witness in Norway and author Webster Tarpley.
